{
  "timestamp_0100": "Client admitted from ED with diagnosis of pre-renal AKI. Client is a recent immigrant, speaks limited English, and relies on his son for translation. Son reports client had vomiting and diarrhea for 3 days and delayed seeking care due to transportation issues. Client oriented to person and place, but not time. Skin turgor poor, mucous membranes dry. IV of 0.9% sodium chloride initiated at 125 mL/hr.",
  "timestamp_0800": "Urine output for last 8 hours is 120 mL. Client reports nausea has subsided but now complains of numbness and tingling in his hands and around his mouth. States he feels 'weak and heavy.' Appears lethargic. Lungs clear to auscultation bilaterally."
}

{
  "type": "12-Lead ECG Interpretation",
  "timestamp": "0945",
  "findings": "Sinus bradycardia at 58 bpm. P waves present. PR interval normal. QRS complex is widened at 0.14 seconds. T waves are tall and peaked. No ST segment elevation or depression noted."
}

